Edmund Keating Hyland (Irish: Éamonn Céitinn Ó Haoláin; 1780 – 1845) was an Irish uilleann piper of the early 19th century.
Keating Hyland was born in Cahir around 1780.
He composed the famous jig entitled "The Fox Chase" (based on an earlier eight-bar work, Maidrin Ruadh), and performed it before King George IV in 1821.
He died in Dublin in 1845, aged 65.
